<title>USA: Clinton asks for FCC study on curbing liquor ads.</title>
<headline>Clinton asks for FCC study on curbing liquor ads.</headline>
<dateline>WASHINGTON 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>President Bill Clinton on Tuesday asked the Federal Communications Commission to study ways to curb television liquor ads following the industry's decision to abandon its nearly half-century voluntary ban.</p>
<p>&quot;Liquor has no business with kids, and kids should have no business with liquor. Liquor ads on television would provide a message of encouragement to drink that young people simply don't need. Nothing good can come of it,&quot; Clinton said.</p>
</text>
